item.title: CVE-2018-19956|2024-09-16T17:08:36.080Z -- qnap%20systems%20inc. -- photo%20station
item.description: The cross-site scripting vulnerability has been reported to affect earlier versions of Photo Station. If exploited, the vulnerability could allow remote attackers to inject malicious code. This issue affects: QNAP Systems Inc. Photo Station versions prior to 5.7.11; versions prior to 6.0.10.

item.title: CVE-2021-34356|2024-09-16T16:52:47.065Z -- qnap%20systems%20inc. -- photo%20station
item.description: A cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability has been reported to affect QNAP device running Photo Station. If exploited, this vulnerability allows remote attackers to inject malicious code. We have already fixed this vulnerability in the following versions of Photo Station: Photo Station 6.0.18 ( 2021/09/01 ) and later
